	  b quest_dialog = true;
		screen_text = "You seem to take pleasure in investigating curious occurences, do you? Not a rare trait for a traveller, I presume. You see, there is this particular pond just a little bit along the way, located in an alcove to to your right. There are rumors that dropping a gold coin in it will grant you a wish of any kind. As tempting as it may sound, woe to those who try doing that. The gold coins attract attention of the Pond keeper. I do not know his name, but he certainly loves to challenge his summoners to a friendly potentially lethal duel. If you wish to prove your skills, you may try challenging him, too. Even one gold coin is enough. Be wary, for he does not return the offerings. You may need to drop a coin several times, as he sends his minions first to see if you're even worth duelling. I used to meet him in a friendly fight from time to time, but at some point I ran out of gold. I should not be visiting casinos, I guess. Oh, and I have another matter to discuss with you, if you'd care.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
