	{
		activate_quest* = c24_slice_2_quest_krug_merchant,0;
	  b quest_dialog = true;
		screen_text = "Greetings, traveler. Dartakk is the name. I can tell you're a decent sort because you did not run away when spoken to. You see, I am here to fulfill my dying father's wish. He grabbed me by my hand and said 'I want you to become merchant'. His was a little hard to hear. It is also quite possible that he said 'I become enchant'. He was dying of a witch's curse, you see. But that's another story. Anyway, a wish is a wish, and I decided to honor it. I set out for the town of Frostfingers, to learn how to do merchanting right. You see, a few moments ago, I tried to help this traveler pushing a cart across this bridge. However, he panicked, and pressed his mules harder to pull his cart. A little too harder, it seems. The mules misstepped and fell down onto the stalagmites along with the cart. The man looked at the scene in horror, and started to run. I understand it is hard to believe that such low price for Phrak bacon is suspicious, but I think he overreacted. I would like to set things right with him. He murmured something about being home soon to one of the mules before I approached them. Listen, would you mind dropping a good word for me? He probably lives nearby. I believe a third person might reason with him more successfully. I cannot become a merchant with such a debt with a potential customer.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
